definition.value: A role played by a compound in a fluid state in swelling a gel, network, or solid.
A role played by a compound that facilitates the rapid drying of gels without their cracking.
Polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons consisting of fused benzene rings in a rectilinear arrangement and their substitution derivatives.
Compounds containing a tetracene skeleton.
Compounds containing a pentacene skeleton.
Compounds containing a hexacene skeleton.
Compounds containing a heptacene skeleton.
Compounds containing an octacene skeleton.
Compounds containing a nonacene skeleton.
Compounds of general formula RR'NC(=S)NR''R'''.
A compound of general formula RC(=O)SR'. Compare with thionoester, RC(=S)OR'.
A compound of general formula RC(=S)OR'. Compare with thioester, RC(=O)SR'.

A 1,4-benzodiazepinone that is 1,3-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzodiazepin-2-one substituted by a 2-(diethylamino)ethyl group, 2-fluorophenyl group and chloro group at positions 1, 5 and 7, respectively. It is a partial agonist of GABAA receptors and used for the treatment of insomnia.
A ketoaldonic acid derivative derivative that is a seven-membered ketoaldonic acid having an amino substituent at the 2-position and the 3- and 7-positions deoxygenated.
A 2-oxo aldehyde consisting of pyruvaldehyde having a phosphooxy group at the 3-position.
A ketohexose monophosphate having keto groups at the 2- and 5-positions, hydroxy groups at the 3- and 4-positions and the phosphate group at the 6-position.
Quinones containing an acene fused ring system.
Acenes containing two aldehyde groups.
Acenes containing aldehyde groups.
Acenes containing two aldehyde groups at the 2 and 3 positions.
Acenes containing two aldehyde groups at the 9 and 10 positions.
Acenes containing two nitrile groups.
Acenes containing nitrile groups.
Acenes containing two nitrile groups at the 2 and 3 positions.
A chloroolefin that is cyclohexa-1,4-diene substituted by chloro groups at positions 1, 3, 4 and 6.

A monocarboxylic acid that is a 2-fluoro-[1,1'-biphenyl-4-yl] moiety linked to C-2 of propionic acid. A non-steroidal anti-inflammatory, analgesic and antipyretic, it is used as a pre-operative anti-miotic as well as orally for arthritis or dental pain.
Any acene dinitrile carrying cyano groups at positions 9 and 10.
An anthracenedinitrile carrying cyano groups at positions 9 and 10.
Acenes containing two ester groups.
Members of the class of acenes containing ester groups.
A diester is a compound containing two ester groups.
A dinitrile is a compound containing two nitrile groups.
The N(2)-succinoyl derivative of L-citrulline.
